Name: wholly
Version: 1.0.1
Summary: Wholly
Home-page: https://github.com/SRI-CSL/Wholly
Author: Loic Gelle, Hassen Saidi, Ian A. Mason.
Author-email: iam@csl.sri.com
License: MIT
Description: Wholly provides a Python tool that can build clean packages in a traceable way from open-source code. We make use of Docker containers to provide a minimal and controlled build environment, clear and meaningful build "recipes" to describe precisely the dependencies and the build invocations, and fine-grained sub-packaging to release lightweight and usable images.
